<div id="first_time" class="dashboard">
	<div id="welcome">
		<h2>Welcome!</h2>
		<p>
			Hello and welcome to Pursuit&trade;, Trigon Solutions' prospect management application.  Pursuit enables Trigon Expert Scheduling personnel to access the central repository 
			of leads, manage workflow, and schedule sales presentations and expert sessions.  The application also provides details financial reports so that you can monitor your 
			effectiveness and increase sales.  
		</p>
		<p>
			As most Expert Schedulers are working remotely, the Pursuit application is often the primary means of day-to-day communication between the scheduler and the company.  
			Important notices and updates will appear on this page regularly.  <span class="strong">Please read the updates as they appear and stay current, as this will directly
			affect your effectiveness as a Trigon employee.</span>
		</p>
	</div>
	<div id="getting_started">
		<h2>Getting Started</h2>
		<p>
			To get started, first-time users should become familiar with Trigon's sales process and other aspects of operations.  To do so, please read the following (designated order
			is not required, but recommended)[ NOTE: these are PDF files, so Adobe's Acrobat Reader software is required.  You may download this 
			<%= link_to 'here', 'http://get.adobe.com/reader/' %>]:
			<ul>
				<li><%= link_to 'The Sales Process', pdf_path('sales_process'), :target => '_blank' %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Making Money', pdf_path('making_money'), :target => '_blank' %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Managing the Conversation', pdf_path('managing_the_conversation'), :target => '_blank' %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Closing the Sale', pdf_path('closing_the_sale'), :target => '_blank' %></li>
			</ul>
		</p>
		<p>
			Now that you're familiar with the general sales process, we have provided a brief introduction to the Pursuit application, as well as some more in-depth documentation
			outlining the various features of the system.
			<ul>
				<li><%= link_to 'Quick Start', quick_start_path(:height => 500, :width => 500), :class => 'thickbox' %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'User Guide', users_guide_url(:height => 500, :width => 500), :class => 'thickbox' %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Documentation', documentation_url(:height => 500, :width => 500), :class => 'thickbox' %></li>
			</ul>
		</p>
		<p>
			So now you're ready.  Good luck, and let's get started!  <%= link_to 'Create a Call Queue', new_user_call_queue_url(current_user) %>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>